 well as the wartime celebrity community Chung cultivated. Her life affords a rare glimpse into the possibilities of traversing racial, gender, and sexual boundaries of American society from the late Victorian era through the early Cold War period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChinese American physicians - Biography. 0aChinese American physiciansvBiography. 0aChinese American physicians. 0aChinese American womenzUnited StatesvBiography. 0aChinese American women. 0aChung, Margaret. 0aMedicine. 0aWomen physicianszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aWomen physicians. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh  a20th century.  aallied forces.  aamerican history.  abiographical.  abiography.  acelebrity community.  acelebrity.  achinatown.  achinese americans.  acultural history.  acultural studies.  adr margaret chung.  afemale physician.  aflyboys.  ahollywood.  amom chung.  amovie stars.  apolitical figures.  apoliticians.  aqueer history.  asailors.  asan francisco.  asocial studies.  asoldiers.  aunited states.  awar historians.  awartime america.  awartime.  awestern medicine.  awomens studies.  aworld war ii.  awwii.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093892240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938922423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938922/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles